org.apache.commons.lang3.math.Fraction does not reduce (Integer.MIN_VALUE, 2^k)
The greatestCommonDivisor method in class Fraction does not find the gcd of Integer.MIN_VALUE and 2^k, and this case can be triggered by taking Integer.MIN_VALUE as the numerator. Note that the case of taking Integer.MIN_VALUE as the denominator is handled explicitly in the getReducedFraction factory method. FractionTest.java  // additional test cases  public void testReducedFactory_int_int() {   // ...   f = Fraction.getReducedFraction(Integer.MIN_VALUE, 2);   assertEquals(Integer.MIN_VALUE / 2, f.getNumerator());   assertEquals(1, f.getDenominator());   public void testReduce() {   // ...   f = Fraction.getFraction(Integer.MIN_VALUE, 2);   result = f.reduce();   assertEquals(Integer.MIN_VALUE / 2, result.getNumerator());   assertEquals(1, result.getDenominator());   